# Project Rules for AI Coding Agents

This file defines how git commits, branches, and releases are managed in this project.
Copy this to `CLAUDE.md` in your repo root and customize.

---

## Commit Message Format

Every commit must follow this 5-part structure:

```
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary — max 72 chars>

CONTEXT: <what state the code was in BEFORE this change>
CHANGE:  <exactly what was done>
WHY:     <the reason — business or technical motivation>
IMPACT:  <what this enables or unblocks>

<footer: Closes #N | BREAKING CHANGE | Refs #N>
```

### Examples

```
feat(auth): add Google OAuth2 login with PKCE flow

CONTEXT: Only email/password login existed, causing 40% signup abandonment on mobile.
CHANGE:  Implements OAuth2 PKCE flow with Google Identity Services SDK.
WHY:     Users expect social login. PKCE is mandatory for mobile SPAs.
IMPACT:  Enables one-tap login on mobile. Reduces signup friction in Phase 2 rollout.

Closes #178
```

```
fix(payments): prevent double-charge on webhook retry

CONTEXT: Stripe delivered webhooks twice under load due to 30s timeout.
CHANGE:  Adds idempotency_key to all Stripe charge requests.
WHY:     Stripe-native deduplication is simpler than Redis-based alternatives.
IMPACT:  Eliminates billing support tickets for duplicate charges.

Closes #301
```

### Types

| Type | Usage |
|------|-------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code restructure (no behavior change) |
| `test` | Add/update tests |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `chore` | Config, deps, tooling |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `security` | Security fix |
| `hotfix` | Urgent production fix |
| `release` | Version bump / release |

### Project-Specific Scopes

<!-- Replace with your project's module/package names -->
- `api`
- `ui`
- `db` / `database`
- `auth`
- `payments`
- `infra`
- `cli`
- `core`

---

## Branch Naming Convention

| Branch Pattern | Purpose |
|----------------|---------|
| `main` | Production — protected, no direct commits |
| `develop` | Integration branch |
| `feature/<description>` | New features (branch from develop) |
| `fix/<description>` | Bug fixes (branch from main) |
| `hotfix/<description>` | Urgent production fixes (branch from main) |
| `chore/<description>` | Maintenance tasks |
| `release/v<version>` | Release preparation |

---

## PR Requirements

- [ ] Tests pass (run: `npm test` or the project's test command)
- [ ] No secrets or credentials in the diff
- [ ] Linked to an open issue (Closes #N / Fixes #N)
- [ ] Created as draft by default (promote when ready)
- [ ] No direct pushes to `main` or `develop`
- [ ] Breaking changes have `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer
- [ ] Docs updated if behavior changed

### Test Command

<!-- Replace with your project's test command -->

```bash
npm test
```

---

## Forbidden

- ❌ `git add .` without reviewing what's being staged
- ❌ Committing `node_modules/`, `.env`, `*.pem`, `*.key`
- ❌ Direct pushes to `main`
- ❌ Committing secrets or credentials (even on private branches)

---

## Release Process

1. Run `bash scripts/generate-changelog.sh` to update CHANGELOG.md
2. Bump version in package.json / pyproject.toml
3. Commit: `release: bump version to v<version>`
4. Tag: `git tag -a v<version> -m "Release v<version>"`
5. Push: `git push origin main --tags`

